This is the OpenUH OpenACC compiler Alpha Release. So there will be some bugs
in the code. HPC Tools of Computer Science Department in University of Houston
doesn't take any responsibility due to these bugs.

We are still working on OpenACC compiler, to make it more robust. Here are the
instructions to building the OpenUH OpenACC compiler.
###########################################################
Building the OpenUH OpenACC
###########################################################

1. make a new dir for building the OpenUH OpenACC version, 
e.g: mkdir build-openacc

and then "cd build-openacc"

2. configure the file, openacc folder is the OpenUH OpenACC source. The reason
use the debug version is that compiler outputs more information. If you have
any compiler bugs, please send us your code and bug information(Compiler's
output).
../openacc/configure --prefix=/PATH/WHERE/COMPILER/INSTALL/
--with-build-optimize=debug --with-cuda=/PATH/TO/CUDA/

e.g:
../openacc/configure --prefix=/home/daniel/opt/openacc/ 
 15 --with-build-optimize=debug --with-cuda=/opt/cuda/5.0/

3. then, run "make"

###########################################################
LIMITATION
###########################################################
This is the baseline version of OpenACC compiler. Here are the limitations.
1.No multi-dimensional array support
2.No structure support
3.No OpenACC parallel, host_data, declare, cache, async
4.Only suports C Front-end OpenACC







